title: 150 dolphins dead in Amazon; scientists blame 102-degree water
description: The mass die-off of the endangered pink dolphins in Brazil’s Lake Tefé could be linked to climate change and the El Niño phenomenon, they said.

title: Ukrainian journalist missing in Russian-occupied territory
description: Victoria  Roshchyna was last heard from on Aug. 3, according to the IWMF, which said in a statement that it was “extremely concerned for her safety.”

title: Has the war in Ukraine changed Macron? Allies would love to know.
description: Over the past several months French President Emmanuel Macron has strongly backed Ukraine to join both NATO and the E.U., but allies are wary if this change is for the long term.

title: Most favor military aid to Ukraine, but partisan split grows, poll finds
description: The findings come at a pivotal moment, as Ukraine, struggling to retake territory, seeks further U.S. commitment with no end to the war in sight.

title: Pope Francis scolds U.S., ‘irresponsible’ Western lifestyle in climate plea
description: The “green pope” denounced the scale of emissions from high-consumption cultures and argued that the world’s poor were paying the price.

title: Ukraine live briefing: U.S. contends with chaos in Congress, uncertainty over Ukraine aid
description: Rep. Kevin McCarthy (R-Calif.) was ousted as House speaker Tuesday, at a time when some Republicans are balking at further aid for Ukraine.

title: Canada elects first Black speaker of the House of Commons
description: Greg Fergus, who chairs Parliament’s Black Caucus, beat six other candidates. He replaces Anthony Rota, who resigned after uproar over the honoring of a Nazi veteran.

title: Worst dengue outbreak on record in Bangladesh kills more than 1,000
description: At least 1,030 people have died, and more than 210,000 have been infected in Bangladesh so far this year, compared with just 281 deaths for all of 2022.

title: In Ukraine, explosive DIY drones give an intimate view of killing
description: The drones are fast and stream video to goggles to give the operator a cockpit view. They are now the predominant attack drone in Ukraine.

title: Five years after Khashoggi murder, lots of geopolitics, little justice
description: Five years since the assassination of Jamal Khashoggi, a Saudi journalist and Washington Post contributor, the world has failed to hold Saudi Arabia accountable.
